== Roasted Potatoes ==

Preheat your #oven{} to 200°C. Chop the @Salad Potatoes{350%g} into 2cm chunks
and pop on a large lined #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{} and season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat then spread out and roast on the top shelf
of your oven until golden and crispy, ~{30-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through
cooking.

Meanwhile, drain and rinse the @chickpeas{1%400g can} in a #sieve{}.
Shell and roughly chop the @Pistachios{40%g}. Roughly chop half the
@Dried Cranberries{30%g}.

== Chickpea Burgers ==

Pop the chickpeas, chopped cranberries and half the pistachios into a
#mixing bowl{}. Add the @Plain Flour{24%g}, half the @Redcurrant Jelly{50%g}
and a good pinch of salt and pepper. Use a #fork{} or #masher{} to mash
everything together until the chickpeas are well crushed and you have a thick
textured paste-like mixture. Using your hands, squish the mixture into one
burger per person, about the same width as the bun. Pop the burgers on a
#plate{} and refrigerate.

== Festive Slaw ==

Meanwhile, halve the @Apple{1}, remove the core then slice thinly. Trim the
@Spring Onion{2} and thinly slice. Pop the apple, spring onion, remaining
pistachios and cranberries into another mixing bowl along with the
@Coleslaw Mix{120%g}.

In a #small bowl{}, mix together the @Low Fat Natural Yoghurt{150%g},
@Red Wine Vinegar{12%g}, @Dijon Mustard{1/2%tsp} and half the
@Mayonnaise{1}. Season with a good pinch of salt and plenty of pepper then
add to the bowl of slaw ingredients. Use your hands to combine everything
well. Set aside.

== Cooking ==

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on medium heat. When hot,
carefully lay in the chickpea burgers and fry until golden brown,
~{3-4%minutes} on each side, turning occasionally.

Meanwhile, halve the @Burger Buns{2}, place on another baking tray and warm
through on the top shelf of your oven for a few minutes.

== To Serve ==

When you're ready to serve, spread a little of the remaining redcurrant jelly
on the base of the burger bun and the rest of the mayonnaise on the lid. Lay
the chickpea burger inside. Serve the burgers alongside plenty of festive
slaw and roasted potatoes. Enjoy!